289ctt-0002ctt-0002.xmlNotes on Cubical Type Theory2024823Trey Plante
Cubical type theory is a constructive approach to homotopy type theory that is meant to give a computation character to HoTT.
Roughly speaking, cubical type theory extends Martin-Lof type theory with a pretype, \mathbb {I}, that is interpreted as the abstract interval.
The reason for extending type theory with this structure is to construct a type theory with the semantic properties of HoTT without sacrificing
all the syntactic properties that imbue dependent type theory with computational character.291ctt-0005ctt-0005.xmlCofibration Logic for Directed Type TheoryDefinition202494Trey Plante
