299ctt-0006ctt-0006.xmlBranch on CofibrationsDefinition2024911
The branch on cofibrations is an expression in cubical type theory that creates conditional evaluation based on the validity of a given formula
    within a given context. We write  [e_{1}, e_{2}]_{\alpha , \beta }  to indicate the branch expression on \alpha  and \beta  with e_{1} and e_{2}
    as values of the branch. The expression is analagous to the common case expression on coproducts seen in dependent type theory.\usepackage {ebproof}
     \usepackage {mathtools}
     \usepackage {amsmath}
        \DeclareMathOperator {\cof }{cof}
     \DeclareMathOperator {\A }{A}
     \DeclareMathOperator {\sU }{\mathcal {U}}
     \DeclareMathOperator {\inb }{in}
     \DeclareMathOperator {\outb }{out}
     \DeclareMathOperator {\bPsi }{\mathbf {\Psi }}

    \begin {prooftree}
            \hypo {\Gamma  \vdash  A : \sU _{l}} \hypo {\Gamma  \vdash _{\bPsi } \alpha  \lor  \beta } \hypo {\Gamma , \alpha  \vdash  e_{1} : A} \hypo {\Gamma , \beta  \vdash  e_{2} : A}
            \hypo {\Gamma , \alpha , \beta  \vdash  e \equiv  f : A}
            \infer 5[intro]{\Gamma  \vdash  [e_{1}, e_{2}]_{\alpha , \beta } : A}
    \end {prooftree}

    \usepackage {ebproof}
