Paraphrased from n-Lab:

    The \eta  law says that if we unpack a term of type A + B and then use the resulting term only to repackage it as a term of type
    A + B, then we can skip the unpacking. We obtain the weak \eta  law by specifying the resulting type as  A + B and u := z.
